decision_conditions:
CONDITION 14. The whole scheme shall achieve at least a 40% reduction in total (regulated and unregulated) CO2 emissions, in comparison to total emissions from a baseline scheme that complies with the Building Regulations 2006. In order to deliver this CO2 reduction, the whole development should deliver as a minimum; 13% CO2 reduction from energy efficiency measures, 29% CO2 reduction from CHP installation and a 1% CO2 reduction from PV installation. Details of the renewable energy technologies shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to any infrastructure works commencing on site. The details shall include:
 
a) the resulting scheme, together with any flue/stack details, machinery/operations location, specification and operational detail;
 
b) an energy assessment confirming that the resulting scheme shall provide for the above mentioned relevant carbon dioxide savings on site;
 
c) a management plan and maintenance strategy/schedule for the operation of the technologies;
 
d) a servicing plan including times, location, frequency, method.

The development shall be carried out strictly in accordance with the details so approved, shall be maintained as such thereafter and no change there from shall take place without the prior written consent of the Local Planning Authority.

REASON: In the interest of sustainable development and to ensure that the Local Planning Authority may be satisfied that the renewable energy targets are met, and to accord with policy 4A.7 of the London Plan (Consolidated with Alterations since 2004).
